Minimum Specifications:
Operating System: Android 8.0 (Oreo) or later, iOS 13.0 or later.
Processor: Quad-core 1.5 GHz or higher.
RAM: 2 GB or more.
Storage: 200 MB free space (initial installation), with additional space for notes and cached data.
Internet Connectivity: Required for initial setup, synchronization, and AI Chatbot functionality. Offline capabilities are supported for note and task management, with data syncing upon reconnection.

How to Install:

For Android Devices:
Open the Google Play Store app on your device.
In the search bar at the top, type "StudySync" and press Enter.
Locate the "StudySync - Academic Organizer" app (or similar name) by "[Developer Name - e.g., StudySync Inc.]" and tap on it.
Tap the "Install" button.
Once the installation is complete, tap "Open" to launch the app, or find the StudySync icon on your home screen or app drawer.

For iOS Devices:
Open the App Store app on your iPhone or iPad.
Tap the "Search" tab at the bottom right of the screen.
In the search bar at the top, type "StudySync" and tap "Search."
Find the "StudySync" and tap on it.
Tap the "Get" button (it might show a cloud icon with a downward arrow if you've downloaded it before) and then authenticate with Face ID, Touch ID, or your Apple ID password if prompted.
